Comment: Organized at Camp Parapet, La., April 28, 1863, as the 1st Engineers, Corps d'Afrique, in August, 1863
Changed from 1st MS Colored HA to 4th US Colored HA in March 1864
organized with Rigby's Battery "A" Light Artillery (also involved in this campaign)
Includes Sherer's (Smith's) Independent Cavalry Company as Company B

Detachment: Colvin's Independent Battery (Colvin's Battery Light Artillery was transferred and assigned as Battery K, First Regiment Illinois Light Artillery, in pursuance of General Orders No. 47, Headquarters State of Illinois, Adjutant General's Office, dated Mar. 23, 1865)
Reorganization of Bookwood's Independent Battery Light Artillery
